    (?? "‚ĖĄ‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ĖĄ " "‚ĖÄ‚ĖÄ‚Ėź‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ĖĆ" "  ‚Ėą‚Ėą  " "  ‚ĖĄ‚ĖĄ  ")
    (?: " " "‚ĖĄ" " " "‚ĖĄ")
    (?& "‚ĖĄ‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ĖĄ  " "‚Ėź‚Ėą‚ĖĄ‚Ėą‚ĖĆ " "‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ĖÄ‚Ėą‚ĖĄ‚Ėą" "‚ĖÄ‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ĖĄ‚Ėą‚ĖĆ")
    (?, " " " " "‚ĖĄ" "‚ĖÄ")
    (?. " " " " " " "‚ĖĄ")
    (?! "‚Ėą‚ĖĆ" "‚Ėą‚ĖĆ" "‚ĖÄ " "‚ĖĄ ")
    (?' "‚Ėą‚ĖĆ" "‚ĖÄ " " " " ")
    (?- "  " "‚ĖĄ‚ĖĄ" "  " "  ")
    (?\s "  " "  " "  " "  "))
  "The lameblock font: (CHAR ROW1 ROW2 ROW3 ROW4).")

(defconst lameserver--hues ["pink" "purple" "cyan" "green" "orange"]
  "Accent hue families; each phile gets one, seeded from its number.")

(defun lameserver--hue (entry)
  (aref lameserver--hues
        (lameserver--seed (concat "hue" (plist-get entry :phile-hex)
                                  (plist-get entry :slug))
                          (length lameserver--hues))))

(defun lameserver--block-glyph (ch)
  (cdr (assq (downcase ch) lameserver--lameblock)))

(defun lameserver--block-words (text)
  "TEXT as a list of words; each word is (WIDTH . GLYPH-LIST)."
  (let ((words '()))
    (dolist (word (split-string (downcase text) " " t))
      (let ((glyphs (delq nil (mapcar #'lameserver--block-glyph
                                      (string-to-list word)))))
        (when glyphs
          (push (cons (apply #'+ (mapcar (lambda (g)
                                           (apply #'max (mapcar #'length g)))
                                         glyphs))
                      glyphs)
                words))))
    (nreverse words)))

(defun lameserver--block-logo (text &optional hue max-cols)
  "TEXT in the lameblock font: a <pre> of shaded letterforms.
HUE names the accent family (nil = newsletter gray); wraps at MAX-COLS."
  (let* ((max-cols (or max-cols 64))
         (space-w 3)
         (lines '())     ; bands of words
         (line '()) (line-w 0)
         (letter -1))
    (dolist (word (lameserver--block-words text))
      (let ((w (car word)))
        (when (and line (> (+ line-w space-w w) max-cols))
          (push (nreverse line) lines)
          (setq line '() line-w 0))
        (push word line)
        (setq line-w (+ line-w (if (cdr line) space-w 0) w))))
    (when line (push (nreverse line) lines))
    (setq lines (nreverse lines))
    (let* ((width (apply #'max 1 (mapcar
                                  (lambda (l)
                                    (+ (apply #'+ (mapcar #'car l))
                                       (* space-w (1- (length l)))))
                                  lines)))
           (out '()))
      (dolist (l lines)
        ;; letters alternate two shades of the hue; the counter runs
        ;; per band so all four rows of a glyph agree
        (let ((band-start (1+ letter)))
          (dotimes (row 4)
            (let ((cells '()) (li (1- band-start)))
              (dolist (word l)
                (unless (eq word (car l))
                  (push (make-string space-w ?\s) cells))
                (dolist (g (cdr word))
                  (cl-incf li)
                  (let* ((line-str (nth row g))
                         (gw (apply #'max (mapcar #'length g)))
                         (padded (concat line-str
                                         (make-string (- gw (length line-str)) ?\s))))
                    (push (format "<span class=\"%s\">%s</span>"
                                  (cond ((= row 3) "sh")
                                        ((cl-evenp li) "hi")
                                        (t "lo"))
                                  (lameserver--escape padded))
                          cells))))
              (when (= row 3) (setq letter li))
              (push (apply #'concat (nreverse cells)) out)))))
      ;; a dust line under the piece, seeded from the text
      (let ((state (string-to-number
                    (substring (secure-hash 'sha1 text) 0 8) 16))
            (dust '()))
        (dotimes (_ width)
          (setq state (lameserver--xorshift state))
          (push (aref "  ¬∑  ‚ĖĎ ‚Ėí  ‚ĖÄ ‚ĖĄ   .      " (mod state 23)) dust))
        (push (format "<span class=\"sh\">%s</span>"
                      (apply #'string (nreverse dust)))
              out))
      (format "<pre class=\"lb%s\" style=\"--cols:%d\" aria-hidden=\"true\">%s</pre>"
              (if hue (concat " hue-" hue) "")
              width
              (string-join (nreverse out) "\n")))))

;;;; ---------------------------------------------------------------- drip edge

;; The file_id.diz melt: a solid mass along the top that drips down into
;; ‚ĖĎ‚Ėí‚Ėď hangers of clustered, irregular length.  Wider than any viewport so
;; it clips at the box edge.  Rendered as one <pre>; four rows.

(defconst lameserver--drip-cols 220 "Drip width in cells; clips to the box.")

(defun lameserver--drip (&optional seed-string)
  "A drip edge <pre>, its hangers seeded deterministically from SEED-STRING."
  (let* ((cols lameserver--drip-cols)
         (seed (or seed-string "drip"))
         (state (string-to-number (substring (secure-hash 'sha1 seed) 0 8) 16))
         (heights (make-vector cols 0))
         (cur 1)
         (rows '()))
    (when (zerop state) (setq state 305419896))
    ;; a smoothed random walk of hanger lengths (0..3), with occasional
    ;; long single drips for that hand-drawn irregularity
    (dotimes (c cols)
      (setq state (lameserver--xorshift state))
      (setq cur (max 0 (min 3 (+ cur (- (mod state 3) 1)))))
      (when (zerop (mod state 17)) (setq cur 3))
      (aset heights c cur))
    ;; row 0 is the solid mass; rows 1..3 are the fading hangers
    (dotimes (r 4)
      (let ((line (make-string cols ?\s t)))    ; multibyte: cells are blocks
        (dotimes (c cols)
          (let ((h (aref heights c)))
            (aset line c
                  (cond ((= r 0) ?‚Ėą)
                        ((< r h) (aref "¬∑‚Ėď‚Ėí‚ĖĎ" r))     ; mid-hanger
                        ((= r h) (aref "¬∑‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ¬∑" r))     ; the tip
                        (t ?\s)))))
        (push (lameserver--escape line) rows)))
    (format "<pre class=\"drip\" aria-hidden=\"true\">%s</pre>"
            (string-join (nreverse rows) "\n"))))

;;;; ---------------------------------------------------------------- phile head

(defun lameserver--issue-bar (entry)
  "The newsletter issue bar: ‚ĖĆ phile 0xNN ‚Ēā ... ‚Ēā date ‚Ėź, plus a creds line."
  (let ((date (if (plist-get entry :time)
                  (format-time-string "%B %Y" (plist-get entry :time))
                "undated")))
    (concat
     "<div class=\"issue\" aria-hidden=\"false\">"
     (format "<span class=\"i-cell\">phile %s</span>" (plist-get entry :phile-hex))
     "<span class=\"i-cell i-mid\">an official lameserver public transmission</span>"
     (format "<span class=\"i-cell\">%s</span>" (lameserver--escape date))
     "</div>"
     "<div class=\"issue-sub\">"
     (mapconcat (lambda (tag)
                  (format "<a class=\"tag\" href=\"/category/%s/\">[%s]</a> "
                          (lameserver--slugify tag) (lameserver--escape tag)))
                (plist-get entry :tags) "")
     (format "¬∑ %d min read ¬∑ " (lameserver--reading-time (plist-get entry :words)))
     (if-let* ((sig (plist-get entry :sig)))
         (format (concat "sig <a class=\"sig ok\" href=\"source.org.asc\" "
                         "title=\"gpg --verify source.org.asc source.org\">"
                         "&#10003; 0x%s</a> <a class=\"sig ok\" href=\"/pubkey.asc\">[pubkey]</a>")
                 (substring sig -16))
       "<span class=\"sig none\">sig: none</span>")
     "</div>")))

(defun lameserver--phile-head (entry)
  "Masthead for a phile, ACiD-newsletter style: quote, logo, issue bar."
  (let ((title (plist-get entry :title))
        (desc (plist-get entry :description)))
    (concat
     (format "<header class=\"phile-head hue-%s\">" (lameserver--hue entry))
     (format "<h1 class=\"vh\">%s</h1>" (lameserver--escape title))
     (lameserver--block-logo title (lameserver--hue entry))
     (if (string-blank-p (or desc ""))
         ""
       (format "<div class=\"pre-quote\">&#8216;%s&#8217;</div>"
               (lameserver--escape desc)))
     (lameserver--issue-bar entry)
     (format "<div class=\"sec-drip\">%s</div>" (lameserver--drip title))
     "</header>")))

(defvar lameserver--section-index 0
  "Counts level-1 sections within one phile, to alternate logo side.")

(defun lameserver--html-headline (headline contents info)
  "Top-level org sections open with their name drawn big in lameblock,
floated to alternating sides so the body text wraps around it ‚ÄĒ no box,
newsletter style."
  (let ((out (org-html-headline headline contents info)))
    (if (/= 1 (org-element-property :level headline))
        out
      (let* ((raw (replace-regexp-in-string
                   "[*/=~+_]" "" (or (org-element-property :raw-value headline) "")))
             (side (if (cl-oddp (cl-incf lameserver--section-index)) "left" "right"))
             (logo (lameserver--block-logo raw nil 30)))
        (format "<section class=\"phile-sec float-%s\">%s%s</section>"
                side logo out)))))

;;;; ---------------------------------------------------------------- ANSI art

(defun lameserver--sgr-parse (ansi)
  "Parse chafa ANSI output into a list of (CHAR FG BG), FG/BG \"r;g;b\" or nil."
  (let ((pos 0) (len (length ansi)) (fg nil) (bg nil) (cells '()))
    (while (< pos len)
      (let ((ch (aref ansi pos)))
        (cond
         ;; CSI sequence: ESC [ params final-byte
         ((and (= ch ?\e) (< (1+ pos) len) (= (aref ansi (1+ pos)) ?\[))
          (let ((end (+ pos 2)))
            (while (and (< end len) (not (<= ?@ (aref ansi end) ?~)))
              (setq end (1+ end)))
            (when (and (< end len) (= (aref ansi end) ?m))
              (let ((params (split-string (substring ansi (+ pos 2) end) ";")))
                (while params
                  (pcase (pop params)
                    ((or "0" "") (setq fg nil bg nil))
                    ("39" (setq fg nil))
                    ("49" (setq bg nil))
                    ("38" (when (equal (car params) "2")
                            (pop params)
                            (setq fg (string-join (list (pop params) (pop params) (pop params)) ";"))))
                    ("48" (when (equal (car params) "2")
                            (pop params)
                            (setq bg (string-join (list (pop params) (pop params) (pop params)) ";"))))
                    (_ nil)))))
            (setq pos (1+ end))))
         ((= ch ?\n) (push (list ?\n nil nil) cells) (setq pos (1+ pos)))
         ((= ch ?\r) (setq pos (1+ pos)))
         (t (push (list ch fg bg) cells) (setq pos (1+ pos))))))
    (nreverse cells)))

(defun lameserver--ansi->html (ansi id font-class)
  "Convert ANSI escapes to an HTML fragment: scoped <style> + <pre>.
Adjacent cells with identical style are merged into one span; colors are
deduplicated into per-image classes to keep the output small."
  (let ((classes (make-hash-table :test 'equal))
        (order '())
        (out '())
        (run '())
        (cur 'none))
    (cl-flet ((esc (c) (pcase c (?& "&amp;") (?< "&lt;") (?> "&gt;")
                         (_ (char-to-string c))))
              (flush ()
                (when run
                  (let ((text (apply #'concat (nreverse run))))
                    (push (if (equal cur '(nil . nil))
                              text
                            (let ((cls (or (gethash cur classes)
                                           (let ((c (format "c%d" (hash-table-count classes))))
                                             (puthash cur c classes)
                                             (push (cons c cur) order)
                                             c))))
                              (format "<span class=\"%s\">%s</span>" cls text)))
                          out))
                  (setq run '()))))
      (dolist (cell (lameserver--sgr-parse ansi))
        (pcase-let ((`(,ch ,fg ,bg) cell))
          (if (= ch ?\n)
              (progn (flush) (setq cur 'none) (push "\n" out))
            (let ((style (cons fg bg)))
              (unless (equal style cur) (flush) (setq cur style))
              (push (esc ch) run)))))
      (flush))
    (let ((css (mapconcat
                (lambda (c)
                  (pcase-let ((`(,name . (,fg . ,bg)) c))
                    ;; chafa params are "r;g;b" ‚ÄĒ CSS wants commas
                    (format "#%s .%s{%s%s}" id name
                            (if fg (format "color:rgb(%s);"
                                           (subst-char-in-string ?\; ?, fg))
                              "")
                            (if bg (format "background:rgb(%s);"
                                           (subst-char-in-string ?\; ?, bg))
                              ""))))
                (nreverse order) ""))
          (body (string-trim-right (apply #'concat (nreverse out)))))
      (format "<style>%s</style><pre class=\"ansi-art %s\" id=\"%s\">%s</pre>"
              css font-class id body))))

(defun lameserver--chafa (path size symbols)
  "Run chafa on PATH; return raw ANSI string or nil.
Braille gets fg-only dithered output ‚ÄĒ dot density carries the image;
per-cell backgrounds would wash the dots out on smooth gradients."
  (when-let* ((chafa (lameserver--tool "chafa")))
    (apply #'lameserver--run chafa
           (append (list "--format" "symbols"
                         "--colors" "full"
                         "--symbols" symbols
                         "--size" size)
                   (when (string-match-p "braille" symbols)
                     (list "--fg-only" "--dither" "diffusion"))
                   (list (expand-file-name path))))))

(defun lameserver--ansi-render (path id &optional size symbols)
  "Cached chafa+HTML conversion of image PATH.  Returns HTML or nil."
  (let* ((size (or size (format "%dx999" lameserver--ansi-width)))
         (symbols (or symbols "half+space"))
         (font-class (cond ((string-match-p "braille" symbols) "ansi-braille")
                           ((string-match-p "quad\\|sextant\\|all" symbols) "ansi-argon")
                           (t "ansi-vga")))
         (mtime (file-attribute-modification-time (file-attributes path)))
         (key (secure-hash 'sha1 (format "%s|%s|%s|%s|%s" (expand-file-name path)
                                         (float-time mtime) size symbols
                                         lameserver--converter-version)))
         (cache (lameserver--cache "ansi" (concat key ".html"))))
    (if (file-exists-p cache)
        (let ((html (with-temp-buffer (insert-file-contents cache) (buffer-string))))
          ;; the cached fragment embeds an id; re-target it for this use site
          (replace-regexp-in-string "__ID__" id html t t))
      (when-let* ((ansi (lameserver--chafa path size symbols)))
        (let ((html (lameserver--ansi->html ansi "__ID__" font-class)))
          (when (> (length html) lameserver--ansi-warn-bytes)
            (lameserver--log "lameserver: WARNING %s renders to %dKB of ANSI html"
                             (file-name-nondirectory path) (/ (length html) 1024)))
          (with-temp-file cache (insert html))
          (replace-regexp-in-string "__ID__" id html t t))))))

(defun lameserver--emblem (seed-string &optional w h)
  "Deterministic ANSI block-art emblem for posts without images."
  (let* ((w (or w 22)) (h (or h 11))
         (half (/ (+ w 1) 2))
         (state (string-to-number
                 (substring (secure-hash 'sha1 seed-string) 0 8) 16))
         (chars " ‚ĖĎ‚Ėí‚Ėď‚Ėą‚ĖÄ‚ĖĄ")
         (rows '()))
    (when (zerop state) (setq state 305419896))
    (dotimes (_y h)
      (let ((cells '()))
        (dotimes (_x half)
          (setq state (lameserver--xorshift state))
          (let* ((c (aref chars (mod state (length chars))))
                 (cls (aref lameserver--emblem-classes
                            (mod (ash state -8) (length lameserver--emblem-classes)))))
            (push (cons c (if (eq c ?\s) nil cls)) cells)))
        ;; mirror for that classic logo symmetry
        (let ((left (reverse cells)))
          (push (append left (cdr (reverse left))) rows))))
    (let ((body
           (mapconcat
            (lambda (row)
              (mapconcat
               (lambda (cell)
                 (if (cdr cell)
                     (format "<span class=\"%s\">%c</span>" (cdr cell) (car cell))
                   (char-to-string (car cell))))
               row ""))
            (nreverse rows) "\n")))
      (format "<pre class=\"ansi-art ansi-vga emblem\" aria-hidden=\"true\">%s</pre>" body))))

;;;; ---------------------------------------------------------------- media urls

(defun lameserver--media-url (path org-file)
  "Site-absolute URL for media PATH referenced from ORG-FILE, or nil."
  (let* ((abs (expand-file-name path (file-name-directory org-file)))
         (media-root (file-truename (lameserver--path "org/media"))))
    (when (string-prefix-p media-root (file-truename abs))
      (concat "/media/" (file-relative-name (file-truename abs) media-root)))))

;;;; ---------------------------------------------------------------- export backend

(defvar lameserver--image-counter 0)

(defun lameserver--attr-plist (element)
  "Read #+ATTR_LAMESERVER plist attached to ELEMENT's paragraph."
  (when-let* ((parent (org-element-lineage element '(paragraph))))
    (org-export-read-attribute :attr_lameserver parent)))

(defun lameserver--image-figure (path org-file attrs)
  "Image as pure ANSI text.  The source raster is a build input only ‚ÄĒ
nothing but text ships."
  (let* ((width (min lameserver--ansi-max-width
                     (max 20 (or (and (plist-get attrs :width)
                                      (string-to-number (plist-get attrs :width)))
                                 lameserver--ansi-width))))
         (symbols (or (plist-get attrs :symbols) "half+space"))
         (id (format "ansi%d" (cl-incf lameserver--image-counter)))
         (alt (or (plist-get attrs :alt) (file-name-base path)))
         (ansi (lameserver--ansi-render
                (expand-file-name path (file-name-directory org-file))
                id (format "%dx999" width)
                (pcase symbols
                  ("braille" "braille")
                  ("quad" "quad+half+space")
                  (_ symbols)))))
    (if (not ansi)
        (progn
          (lameserver--log "lameserver: WARNING no ANSI renderer ‚ÄĒ %s dropped" path)
          (format "<pre class=\"ansi-art ansi-missing\">[ image: %s ‚ÄĒ no renderer at build time ]</pre>"
                  (lameserver--escape (file-name-nondirectory path))))
      (format "<figure class=\"ansi-img\" role=\"img\" aria-label=\"%s\">%s</figure>"
              (lameserver--escape alt) ansi))))

(defun lameserver--av-html (path org-file)
  "Audio/video element inside box-drawing chrome."
  (let ((url (or (lameserver--media-url path org-file) path))
        (ext (downcase (or (file-name-extension path) ""))))
    (format "<div class=\"ansi-frame\">%s</div>"
            (if (member ext '("mp3" "ogg" "flac" "wav"))
                (format "<audio controls preload=\"metadata\" src=\"%s\"></audio>" url)
              (format "<video controls preload=\"metadata\" src=\"%s\"></video>" url)))))

(defun lameserver--html-link (link desc info)
  "Intercept media links; delegate everything else to ox-html."
  (let* ((type (org-element-property :type link))
         (path (org-element-property :path link))
         (ext (downcase (or (file-name-extension (or path "")) "")))
         (org-file (plist-get info :input-file)))
    (cond
     ;; images always become ANSI text ‚ÄĒ described or not, nothing raster ships
     ((and (string= type "file")
           (member ext '("png" "jpg" "jpeg" "gif" "webp")))
      (lameserver--image-figure path org-file
                                (append (and desc (list :alt desc))
                                        (lameserver--attr-plist link))))
     ((and (string= type "file")
           (member ext '("mp4" "webm" "mp3" "ogg" "flac" "wav")))
      (lameserver--av-html path org-file))
     ;; rewrite plain file links into org/media to their published URL
     ((and (string= type "file") (lameserver--media-url path org-file))
      (format "<a href=\"%s\">%s</a>"
              (lameserver--media-url path org-file) (or desc path)))
     (t (org-html-link link desc info)))))

